The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro
 Monday, June 07, 2004 				 Girl killed under van wheels
 A STAFF REPORTER																								A two-and-half-year-old girl was crushed under the wheels of a Matador van on Sunday morning, sparking trouble at the intersection of Cossipore Road and Dilawar Jung Road. A mob set the killer vehicle ablaze.																								Ansi Kumari was on her way back home to Narkeldanga after visiting some relatives on Dilawar Jung Road with her grandmother in the morning.																								The Matador, headed for Shyambazar, hit Ansi from behind. Her grandmother was not hurt in the accident.																								The child was rushed to RG Kar Medical College and Hospital where she was declared dead, said an officer of Cossipore police station.																								The driver fled the spot, but people from the area converged on the accident site. They first pelted the van with stones, before torching it.																								The mob then squatted on the road and blocked all traffic to protest rash driving in the area, said the officer from Cossipore thana. When a police contingent reached the spot, it was met by hostile residents protesting cop callousness.																								Ansis parents left their Bipradas Road residence, in Narkeldanga, around 10 am, immediately after receiving news of the tragedy. Their single-storey house was locked all day.
